# Buildoto — Manual setup values, per sprint.
#
# Copy this file to `.env.local` (already git-ignored) and fill it in at the
# END of each sprint. Every value below corresponds to a one-time manual step
# that cannot be automated (OAuth App registration, external accounts, etc.).
#
# Runtime secrets for end-users (Claude API key, GitHub token) are stored in
# the OS keychain via keytar — they do NOT belong in this file.
#
# Loading:
# - Smoke scripts (`pnpm smoke`, `pnpm smoke:project`) read this file via
#   tsx's `--env-file=.env.local`.
# - `pnpm dev` / `pnpm build` inline these values into the main bundle via
#   Vite's `loadEnv()` in `electron.vite.config.ts`.

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# SPRINT 1 — Foundation
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Anthropic API key used ONLY by the smoke tests (`pnpm smoke`,
# `pnpm smoke:project`). At app runtime the user enters their key in the
# Settings dialog and it is stored in the OS keychain via keytar — never here.
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# SPRINT 2 — Project + Git + GitHub
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# GitHub OAuth App Client ID (Device Flow). Public value — safe to commit if
# you ever move it out of .env.local.
#
# How to register:
# 1. https://github.com/settings/applications/new
#    - Application name: Buildoto (or "Buildoto (dev)" for a dev app)
#    - Homepage URL:     https://github.com/<your-org>/buildoto (any stable URL)
#    - Authorization callback URL: any value (Device Flow doesn't use it)
# 2. After creation, tick "Enable Device Flow" in the app's settings.
# 3. Copy the Client ID below. Do NOT generate or paste a Client Secret —
#    Device Flow does not use one.
BUILDOTO_GITHUB_CLIENT_ID=

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# SPRINT 3 — OpenCode embedding + multi-provider + MCP
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# (no manual secrets expected — provider API keys stay in keytar)

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# SPRINT 4 — Polish + packaging + alpha release
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Apple Developer signing (electron-builder notarize). Leave blank for unsigned
# dev builds; fill before publishing the alpha.
# APPLE_ID=
# APPLE_APP_SPECIFIC_PASSWORD=
# APPLE_TEAM_ID=

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# SPRINT 5 — RAG corpus ingestion (backend-only, not the desktop app)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# QDRANT_URL=
# QDRANT_API_KEY=
# OPENAI_API_KEY=            # embeddings model for ingestion

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# SPRINT 6 — Mistral + RAG inference service (backend-only)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# MISTRAL_API_KEY=
# SUPABASE_URL=
# SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY= # backend only — never in the desktop app

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# SPRINT 7 — Stripe billing + portal (backend-only)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=
# STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET=
# STRIPE_PUBLIC_KEY=

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# SPRINT 8 — Buildoto AI provider + v1.0 launch
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# BUILDOTO_AUTH_DEEP_LINK_HOST=   # e.g. auth.buildoto.com
